Pricing Optimization
Pricing Optimization is a project focused on improving a system for obtaining more favorable prices on unissued files.

The Organization
The Organization wants to improve its pricing optimization system.

Logs
Logs are a source of data to be consolidated for pricing optimization.

Bookings
Bookings are a source of data to be consolidated for pricing optimization.

Teams
Teams are the intended users of an operational report generated by the pricing optimization project.

API
API is a source for obtaining data for the optimization script, providing data in .csv format.<SEP>An interface for real data retrieval and for adapting the pipeline for data ingestion.

cdv_log_operation.csv
cdv_log_operation.csv is a file containing logs, used for data joining.<SEP>A CSV file representing a portion of the total data volume to be processed, containing log operations.

cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.csv
cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.csv is a file containing bookings, used for data joining.<SEP>A CSV file representing a portion of the total data volume to be processed, related to air bookings.

listeOptimisation_dd-MM-yyyy.csv
listeOptimisation_dd-MM-yyyy.csv is a generated CSV file containing optimization results.

Exemple rapport optimisation.xlsx
Exemple rapport optimisation.xlsx is an example Excel file used as a reference for filling in required data.<SEP>An Excel file used for building a CSV report and filling in required data.

Automatic Rebookings
Automatic rebookings are part of the current pricing optimization system.

Specific Alerts
Specific alerts are part of the current pricing optimization system.

Files
Files are analyzed one by one in the current pricing optimization approach.

Historical Data
Historical data is not used in the current pricing optimization approach.

Competitive Data
Competitive data is not used in the current pricing optimization approach.

Price Drop Opportunities
Price drop opportunities are detected by the current pricing optimization system as they happen.

Gains
Gains are analyzed as part of the pricing optimization process and are extracted from cdv_log_operation.lgop_results.

Itineraries
Itineraries are analyzed as part of the pricing optimization process.

Day
Day is a factor used for identifying the best optimization opportunities.

Route
Route is a factor used for identifying the best optimization opportunities.

Raw Data
Raw data, including logs and bookings, needs to be joined and structured for pricing optimization.

Relevant Optimizations
Relevant optimizations, specifically those with status 'S', need to be isolated.

Status S
Status S is a filter used to isolate relevant optimizations.

cdv_log_operation.lgop_element_id
cdv_log_operation.lgop_element_id is the join key for cdv_log_operation.csv.

cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.wbkg_reference
cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.wbkg_reference is the join key for cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.csv.

cdv_log_operation.lgop_status
cdv_log_operation.lgop_status is used for record filtering, keeping only rows with status 'S'.

cdv_log_operation.lgop_when
cdv_log_operation.lgop_when represents the Optimization Datetime.<SEP>A column in the cdv_log_operation data that contains optimization datetimes.

cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.dair_code
cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.dair_code represents the Airline.

cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.FromAirportCode
cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.FromAirportCode represents the Start of Trip.

cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.ToAirportCode
cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.ToAirportCode represents the End of Trip.

cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.wbkg_start_date
cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.wbkg_start_date represents the Travel Dates.

cdv_log_operation.lgop_results
cdv_log_operation.lgop_results contains the Gain information.

Average Trends
Average trends are calculated for each airline after extracting the best gains.

Average Gains
Average gains are calculated by time of day for each airline.<SEP>A metric calculated by grouping data based on time of day, day of the week, or combined day+hour.

cdv_log_operation.md
An architecture file for the cdv_log_operation.csv data.

cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.md
An architecture file for the cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.csv data.

topOptimisation.json
A JSON file where the optimization results are to be saved.

Python
The required technology for this project.

SFTP space
A location where CSV and JSON files must be deposited.

GMT+1
A time zone specification for file deposition.

Airline
A type of organization for which optimization gains are to be extracted and analyzed.

Time of Day
A temporal category used for analyzing average gains, ranging from 0 to 23 hours.

Day of the Week
A temporal category used for analyzing average gains, such as Tuesday or Friday.

Combined Day + Hour
A combined temporal category representing specific hours on specific days, used for detailed average gain analysis.

Ranking Slots
A categorization of results sorted by average gain in descending order, keeping the top 3 for each grouping.

Data Volume
A measure of the amount of data to be processed, with provided CSVs representing 20-30% of the total.

Development Environment
The local setup required for project development.

Data Schemas
The structural definitions of the data, which need to be verified.

API Connection
The process of connecting to the API for real data retrieval.

Project Meeting
A meeting with the client to validate the API connection and progress.

Pipeline
A sequence of data processing steps that needs to be adapted for API ingestion.

Schema Compatibility
The degree to which schemas from different sources (CSV and API) are interchangeable.

Unit Tests
Tests performed on individual components of the application.

Performance Tests
Tests conducted to evaluate the application's speed and responsiveness.

Client Feedback
Input provided by the client for making adjustments.

Delivery
The final stage of the project where the application is handed over.

Final Acceptance
The client's formal approval of the delivered application.

Optimization datetime
A timestamp column used for extracting hour and day of the week.

CSV Report
A report generated in CSV format.

JSON Output File
A file containing the results in JSON format.

SFTP Coordinates
The specific details required to access the SFTP space.

Data Order
The sequence in which data must be respected as transmitted in a file.

Development Timeline
A schedule outlining the phases and dates for project development.

Project Launch
The initial phase of the project.

Phase 0
The first phase of the development timeline, focusing on project launch.

Phase 1
The second phase of the development timeline, focusing on development.

Phase 2
The third phase of the development timeline, focusing on API connection and project follow-up.

Phase 3
The fourth phase of the development timeline, focusing on advanced feature development.

Phase 4
The fifth phase of the development timeline, focusing on finalization.

Phase 5
The final phase of the development timeline, focusing on delivery and final acceptance.

September 3-5, 2025
The dates for Phase 0 - Project Launch.

September 8-26, 2025
The dates for Phase 1 - Development.

September 15, 2025
The date when the API for real data retrieval becomes available.

September 16, 2025
The date of a project meeting with the client.

September 17-19, 2025
The dates for Phase 3 - Advanced Feature Development.

September 29 - October 2, 2025
The dates for Phase 4 - Finalization.<SEP>This is a period for finalization, including running unit and performance tests on approximately 1 GB of data and making adjustments based on client feedback.

October 3, 2025
The date for Phase 5 - Delivery and Final Acceptance.<SEP>This date marks the delivery and final acceptance phase, involving putting the application into production on the client's environment and achieving final acceptance.

~1 GB of data
The amount of data used for running unit and performance tests.

September 3
This date signifies the start of development using example files.

September 15
This date marks the availability of the API.

September 16
This date is scheduled for a follow-up meeting.

Production Delivery
This event, scheduled for October 3, signifies the application being put into the client's production environment.

Client
The client is the recipient of the application and is responsible for server configuration and providing feedback.

Application
The application is the software being developed and delivered to the client.

Unit and Performance Tests
These tests are to be run on approximately 1 GB of data as part of the finalization phase.

Adjustments based on client feedback
These are modifications to be made to the application based on input from the client.

Server Configuration
This refers to the setup of the server environment where the application will be deployed, which is handled by the client.
